statements.sql: select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'product_listing' and table_name = 'permissions'

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\Admin'
select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'product_listing' and table_name = 'roles'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\Admin'

with recursive `laravel_cte` as ((select *, 0 as `depth`, cast(`id` as char(65535)) as `path`, cast(`name` as char(65535)) as `name_path`, cast(`slug` as char(65535)) as `slug_path` from `categories` where `parent_id` is null) union all (select `categories`.*, `depth` + 1 as `depth`, concat(`path`, '.', `categories`.`id`), concat(`name_path`, '/', `categories`.`name`), concat(`slug_path`, '/', `categories`.`slug`) from `categories` inner join `laravel_cte` on `laravel_cte`.`id` = `categories`.`parent_id`)) select * from `laravel_cte`
